        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 1:37PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 137 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Tuppers Plains, or near Forked Run State Park, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Forked Run State Park, Tuppers Plains, and Chester.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
